title: 'If humanitarian aid is looted, you cannot distribute it' - UN envoy in Sudan defends delayed response
description: "None of the ceasefires have been respected in total," Volker Perthes, the United Nations special representative for Sudan, has told Sky News.

title: Three pigeon-racing rivals shot dead in dispute
description: A man has shot dead three people in a dispute with rival pigeon racers in Portugal.

title: Leak of unknown gas kills 11 in India
description: Eleven people have died after a gas leak in northern India.

title: Powerful AI systems 'can't be controlled' and 'are already causing harm', says UK expert

title: First humanitarian aid shipment arrives in Port Sudan
description: The first international shipment of humanitarian aid has arrived in Port Sudan following the outbreak of conflict in the country, the International Committee of the Red Cross has said.

title: Freya the celebrity walrus honoured with life-size sculpture after mammal was put down
description: A 600kg walrus which found global fame for her antics in the Oslo fjord before being put down has been honoured with a life-size sculpture.
